<task id="task_vft_g5p_yr">
    <title>Configuring a Flume Destination</title>
    <taskbody>
        <context>
            <p><indexterm>Flume destinations<indexterm>configuring</indexterm></indexterm>Configure
                a Flume destination to write data to Flume. </p>
        </context>
        <steps id="steps_dmg_jyp_yr">
            <step
                conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusableSteps.dita#task_kzs_5vz_sq/1stStep-ReqField-ErrorHandling">
                <cmd/>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>On the <uicontrol>Flume</uicontrol> tab, configure the following
                    properties:</cmd>
                <info>
                    <table frame="all" rowsep="1" colsep="1" id="table_qpb_5yp_yr">
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                            <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/>
                            <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="2.77*"/>
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Flume Property</entry>
                                    <entry>Description</entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Host Configuration</entry>
                                    <entry>Flume host information:<ul id="ul_al4_s1q_yr">
                                            <li>Name - Local alias for the Flume host. </li>
                                            <li>Flume host and port - Host name and port number for
                                                the Flume agent. Use the following format: &lt;host
                                                name>:&lt;port number></li>
                                        </ul>Click <uicontrol>Add</uicontrol> to add additional host
                                        configuration.</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Client Type</entry>
                                    <entry>Flume source client type:<ul id="ul_qcr_fbq_yr">
                                            <li>Avro Failover - Apache Avro Failover RPC
                                                Client.</li>
                                            <li>Avro Load Balancing - Apache Avro LoadBalancing RPC
                                                Client.</li>
                                            <li>Thrift - Apache Thrift RPC Client.</li>
                                        </ul></entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Backoff</entry>
                                    <entry>Temporarily avoid writing to a failed host.<p>Avro Load
                                            Balancing client only. </p></entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Max Backoff (ms)</entry>
                                    <entry>The maximum amount of time to avoid writing to a failed
                                        host. <draft-comment author="Loretta">after which what
                                            happens?</draft-comment><p>Enter the number of
                                            milliseconds between 0 and 65536. </p><p>Use 0 to
                                            trigger the Flume default value of 30000 milliseconds -
                                            30 seconds. </p><p>Avro Load Balancing client only.
                                        </p></entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Host Selection Strategy</entry>
                                    <entry><p>Strategy to select the Flume host to use.</p>Avro Load
                                        Balancing client only. </entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Flume Batch Size (events)</entry>
                                    <entry>Maximum amount of events that the Flume client writes to
                                        a Flume host at one time. The Flume client can split a <ph
                                            conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                                        /> batch into multiple Flume batches that pass data to the
                                        Flume host.</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Flume Client Connection Timeout (ms)</entry>
                                    <entry>Maximum amount of time for the Flume client to connect to
                                        the Flume host. </entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Flume Client Request Timeout (ms)</entry>
                                    <entry>Milliseconds the Flume client waits for a response after
                                        sending data to the Flume host. When the client does not
                                        receive a response in time, the Flume destination resends
                                        the batch, up to the number configured for Max Retry
                                        Attempts.</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Max Retry Attempts</entry>
                                    <entry>Maximum number of times the Flume destination resends
                                        data to Flume and waits for a response before stopping the
                                        pipeline. </entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Retry Wait Time (ms)</entry>
                                    <entry>Milliseconds to wait before resending data to
                                        Flume.</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Data Format</entry>
                                    <entry>Data format for output events:<ul id="ul_ssq_sks_zr">
                                            <li>Text</li>
                                            <li>JSON</li>
                                            <li>Delimited</li>
                                            <li>SDC Record  <xref
                                                  href="../Pipeline_Configuration/SDCRecordFormat.dita#concept_qkk_mwk_br">
                                                  <image href="../Graphics/icon_moreInfo.png"
                                                  scale="10" id="image_ucp_chr_br"/></xref></li>
                                        </ul></entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>Event Charset</entry>
                                    <entry>Character encoding of the events to be processed.</entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>One Event per Batch</entry>
                                    <entry>
                                        <p>Generates a single event for all records in the batch.
                                        </p>
                                    </entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </info>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
